<body>
    <h1>Display the eZ Website Toolbar</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>EZP Version &gt;=3D 5.3</p>
<h2 id=3D"DisplaytheeZWebsiteToolbar-ConfiguringthedisplayoftheWebsiteToolb=
ar">Configuring the display of the Website Toolbar</h2>
<p>To have the regular Webin Toolbar, first add the proper CSS file to your=
 head template : <code>extension/ezwt/design/standard/stylesheets/websiteto=
olbar.css</code></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: xml; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;style type=3D"text/css"&gt;
    @import url("{{ asset('extension/ezwt/design/standard/stylesheets/websi=
tetoolbar.css') }}");
&lt;/style&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Then, in your template, you can add the Webin Toolbar by definining the =
display of the <code>websiteToolbarAction</code> from the <code>exponential_l=
egacy.website_toolbar.controller</code> Controller</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">{% if location is defined %}
    {{ render( controller( "exponential_legacy.website_toolbar.controller:web=
siteToolbarAction", { 'locationId': location.id} ) ) }}
{% endif %}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DisplaytheeZWebsiteToolbar-Redirectionafterpublishing">Redirectio=
n after publishing</h2>
<p>Versions: 5.3.4, 5.4.1.</p>
<p>In order to get properly redirected after publishing or discarding, over=
rides of legacy's&nbsp;<code>content/edit.tpl</code> must include the&nbsp;=
<code>content/edit_redirection.tpl</code>. It adds hidden fields required b=
y legacy for those redirections.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;form method=3D"POST" action=3D"content/edit/..."&gt;
  &lt;!--...--&gt;
  {include uri=3D"design:content/edit_redirection.tpl"}
&lt;/form&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"DisplaytheeZWebsiteToolbar-Aboutthewebsite_toolbarcontroller">Abo=
ut the website_toolbar controller</h3>
<p>The websiteToolbarAction renders the whole Webin Toolbar, and if the log=
ged in user doesn't have the required permission, an empty response is retu=
rned</p>
    </div>
</body>
